If a SI for a given SVSpec is deleted then re-created ...
Option A: SICr builds in this fashion ...
1. Override lingering data. K-merge existing data; then, for every entry, put a tombstone in SICr's output.
2. K-merge primary entries. (Then follow steps for SI creation.) These data override the above overriding of lingering data.
Option B: Each new SI is given a new identity, even if previously another SI existed for the same SVSpec.
(We need a unique integer identifier for each SI anyway, for naming things in filenames (though in the future we might depend less on semantically meaningful filenames).)
We go with option 2 B.
